article_title: In Ohio, 95% of kids have health-insurance coverage
article_text:

article_metadata.description: Nearly 95 percent of Ohio children have health coverage, with the share of uninsured youngsters being reduced by half in the past 15 years. Ohio’s percentage of children with coverage is 2 points above the national average, according to a report released today by the Georgetown University Center for Children and Families, which credits the tax-funded State Children’s Health Insurance Program with driving down the number of uninsured children.
